1.
pyinstaller --onefile --windowed --icon=icon.ico main.py

--onefile: bundles everything into one .exe

--windowed: hides the console window (useful for GUI apps)

--icon=icon.ico: sets your app icon

Make sure icon.ico is in the same directory or provide the full path to it.

2.
To display the same icon in your appâ€™s title bar or taskbar:

self.setWindowIcon(QtGui.QIcon("icon.ico"))
  
Put this inside your main window or widget class (e.g., in initUI()).
